<br>
I am friends with several of the trolls who have been waging the jihad style nonsense of late.  Even though they are friends, I have no problem in letting them know I am disgusted with their actions and attitude of late.  That said, what you did with giving full access to someone who has had an obvious axe to grind here, without any input from the community that you are currently acting as trustee for, is just plain reckless.   It was NOT a smart move, I know you are repentant for it, and I know that your motives were honorable.  I am disgusted with what was done with that information, but I am also relieved that Bog at least did not wipe the boards and go wild on the calenders and rotations. It could have gone far worse.<br>
<br>
This community has endured some of the most idiotic shitstorms (for lack of a better term) then any other server board that exists.  The rathe has always maintained a higher class of players in its pool and it has shone in the system that we have in place.  Recent events have made me highly uncomfortable and I think perhaps we as a whole, not just the admins, reps.  but the entire community needs to find a better way to handle the trend of former players who still want to be a part of the community, but chafe at any rules being placed on them.  <br>
<br>
My suggestion would be the following:<br>
<br>
Add additional, Visible Moderators.. NOT RTA Admins, but moderators whose only access would be day to day patroling of the boards.<br>
<br>
A no tolorance for flaming outside of the flame boards.<br>
<br>
Either complete removal of the CWE area, or a second Free Fire CWE (Flames) area for those whose passions run too hot for self control.<br>
<br>
The rules in flame central would be:<br>
<br>
NO real life information to be posted<br>
NO Porn links or pics<br>
NO direct physical threats<br>
NO Jihad style spamming<br>
and SOME material may be removed on a case by case basis (in order to cover for unforeseen events or material)<br>
<br>
If that is not sufficient, then I might also suggest that perhaps Kluz or Mald might consider hosting the servers flame community with a link to those places.  They seem inclined to host them now, and it might solve the problem with how to decide who is disrupting the community just for the sake of creating chaos, and who honestly and truly feels that they are being oppressed by too many constraints to their opinions.<br>
<br>
One last thing that I would ask, is that since you are the current trustee for the community, that you post a promise, that you will pass over this community rather then sell it to Yantis, because he is contacting every damn board in sight right now, and that is a surefire way to kill this community we have all worked so hard to preserve.<br>
<br>
I appologize if I rambled a bit on this, but I am not usualy this long winded, and do not present myself as well in more then a single sentence.<br>
